## WHAT THE SCRIPT DOES

Reads three MRDS attributes per feature:
  commod1   — primary commodity (e.g. "Gold", "Copper", "Sand and Gravel")
  dep_type  — deposit type (e.g. "tailings", "lode", "placer")
  dev_stat  — development status (e.g. "Producer", "Past Producer", "Prospect")

Runs each row through a priority-ordered classification function.
Writes the result to a new field: category

Classification priority order (top = highest, wins over lower):

  1. Tailings              — dep_type contains "tailings"
  2. Industrial / Noise    — commod1 is purely industrial (gravel, coal, clay,
                             gypsum, etc.) with NO metallic commodity present
  3. Uranium               — commod1 contains "Uranium"
  4. Gemstone              — commod1 contains "Gemstone"
  5. Tier 1 — High-Value Prospect
                           — commod1 is precious (Gold/Silver) or critical mineral
                             AND dev_stat is Prospect or Occurrence
  6. Tier 1 — Active Mine  — same precious/critical commodities but dev_stat
                             is Producer or Plant
  7. Tier 2 — Past Producer— dev_stat is Past Producer AND commod1 is precious
                             or base metal (Cu, Pb, Zn, Mo)
  8. Base Metal Prospect   — commod1 is base metal + dev_stat Prospect/Occurrence
  9. Base Metal — Active   — commod1 is base metal + dev_stat Producer/Plant
 10. Base Metal — Other    — commod1 is base metal, no matching status
 11. Critical Mineral      — commod1 matches critical list (REE, Li, Be, Co, etc.)
                             not already caught above
 12. Prospect — Unclassified  — has Prospect/Occurrence status but no commodity match
 13. Past Producer — Unclassified — has Past Producer status, no commodity match
 14. Active — Unclassified    — has Producer/Plant status, no commodity match
 15. Unclassified           — everything else

Precious metals defined as:   Gold, Silver
Base metals defined as:        Copper, Lead, Zinc, Molybdenum
Critical minerals defined as:  REE, Beryllium, Niobium, Tantalum, Lithium,
                                Vanadium, Cobalt, Tungsten
Noise commodities:             Sand and Gravel, Coal, Clay, Gypsum, Bentonite,
                                Stone Crushed, Peat, Diatomite, Perlite

