  The rest of your Colorado project layers are likely in a projected CRS,
  probably NAD83 / UTM Zone 13N (EPSG:26913) or Colorado State Plane.

What this means:
  QGIS will reproject on-the-fly for display so it will look correct on screen,
  but the layer is NOT in the same native CRS as your other data.
  This matters for:
