REPROJECTION — METHOD

Used QGIS Python Console + native:reprojectlayer processing algorithm.
No GUI export. No layer reload required during reprojection step.

Script used (both layers):

  import processing
  lyr = QgsProject.instance().mapLayersByName("LAYER_NAME")[0]
  src = lyr.source().split("|")[0]   # strip |layername= suffix
  out = src.replace(".gpkg", "_26913.gpkg")
  processing.run("native:reprojectlayer", {
      'INPUT': lyr,
      'TARGET_CRS': 'EPSG:26913',
      'OUTPUT': out
  })

NOTE: First attempt failed — .replace() hit the |layername= string
and produced a corrupted output path. Fixed by splitting on "|" first.

