VIRTUAL FIELDS — LENGTH_MI / AREA_ACRES

Method: addExpressionField() via Python Console.
Virtual fields compute on-the-fly from geometry. No source file modification.
No layer reload required. Fields persist in QGIS project file.

Since all layers are EPSG:26913 (meters), no transform() needed in expressions.

Expressions used:
  Line layers:    round($length / 1609.344, 2)   → Length_mi
  Polygon layers: round($area / 4046.856, 2)     → Area_acres

